summary:
Title: Co-Branding Agreement between 2TheMart Com Inc and i-Escrow Inc

This Co-Branding Agreement, effective from August 26, 1999, outlines the terms between 2TheMart Com Inc and i-Escrow Inc for a one-year period, renewable, regarding their co-branded services. Key obligations include 2TheMart providing materials and services "as is," disclaiming all warranties, and i-Escrow acting in good faith and indemnifying 2TheMart against any claims arising from its acts or misrepresentations. Termination can occur for various reasons, with surviving provisions ensuring completion of pending customer transactions. Notable risks include potential liabilities for breaches and penalties for non-compliance with the agreement's terms.
termination_clause: Termination: Upon any reason, all rights granted under the Agreement terminate, i-Escrow pays all owed amounts to 2TheMart within six weeks, and both parties remove each other's content and marks from their servers. Unless terminated for material breach, all provisions of the Agreement survive to complete pending Customer transactions.
confidentiality_clause: Parties must keep each other's confidential or proprietary information confidential, whether it is disclosed in writing or orally.
liability_clause: Each party disclaims all warranties, express, implied or statutory, including title, non-infringement, merchantability, and fitness for a particular purpose.

summary: This Development Agreement between Aimmune Therapeutics Inc. and Xencor outlines the terms for the development, manufacturing, and commercialization of certain therapeutic products. Key obligations include Aimmune granting Xencor exclusive rights to develop and manufacture the products, while Xencor agrees to provide Aimmune with development and manufacturing services. Both parties must keep confidential all disclosed confidential information and use it only for the purpose of performing under the agreement. Neither party will be liable for lost profits or indirect damages, but Xencor agrees to indemnify Aimmune for any losses arising from breaches of the agreement. Failure to comply with obligations or confidentiality breaches may result in penalties.

liability_clause: Neither party will be liable to the other for any lost profits, special, consequential, incidental, or indirect damages arising from or relating to any breach of this agreement, regardless of any notice of the possibility of such damages. This does not limit or restrict the indemnification rights or obligations of any party under sections 11.1 or 11.2, or damages available for a partyâ€™s breach of confidentiality obligations under Article 12.

summary:
